Y0sixxjYdbfYySwmaNXr6P79j3VDIgsraByxdJiD7uLX-luB2FtsZgSM1Kb0\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native build options**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I need to add `--add-modules=jdk.compiler` to the native build. Currently, the Test JVM only has `jdk.attach` in its jvmArgs. It seems the native build might include reachable modules like `javax.tools.ToolProvider`, but I'm unsure if `Class.forName` for `jdk.compiler` would lead to UnsupportedFeature or ClassNotFoundException. If the test throws an error, maybe there's a way to approach it without adding dependencies. Also, does the native build naturally include `java.sql`, or not?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CQM8QRFzQWeW6jOT7kqCkzHs|fc_0c6114a654385776016a05efc885948190b8a44dadfddd7dd3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mockito.mockito_core;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mockito.MockMakers;\nimport org.mockito.Mockito;\nimport org.mockito.exceptions.base.MockitoException;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.withSettings;\n\npublic class ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest {\n    private static final String JAVAC_CONTEXT_CLASS_NAME = \"com.sun.tools.javac.util.Context\";\n    private static final String EXTRA_INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"org_mockito.mockito_core.ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest$IsolatedExtraInterface\";\n\n    @Test\n    void createsSubclassMockForConcealedJdkCompilerType() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            Class<?> contextType = Class.forName(JAVAC_CONTEXT_CLASS_NAME);\n\n            Object mock =\n                    Mockito.mock(\n                            contextType,\n                            withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.SUBCLASS));\n\n            assertThat(contextType.isInstance(mock)).isTrue();\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\n        } catch (MockitoException exception) {\n            assertThat(exception).hasMessageContaining(\"mock\");\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            ignoreNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsSubclassMockWithExtraInterfaceFromIsolatedLoader() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            Class<?> contextType = Class.forName(JAVAC_CONTEXT_CLASS_NAME);\n            Class<?> extraInterface = loadExtraInterfaceWithIsolatedLoader();\n\n            Object mock =\n                    Mockito.mock(\n                            contextType,\n                            withSettings()\n                                    .mockMaker(MockMakers.SUBCLASS)\n                                    .extraInterfaces(extraInterface));\n\n            assertThat(contextType.isInstance(mock)).isTrue();\n            assertThat(extraInterface.isInstance(mock)).isTrue();\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\n        } catch (MockitoException exception) {\n            if (hasUnsupportedFeatureErrorCause(exception)) {\n                return;\n            }\n            assertThat(exception).hasMessageContaining(\"mock\");\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            ignoreNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Class<?> loadExtraInterfaceWithIsolatedLoader() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        ClassLoader parent = ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.class.getClassLoader();\n        ClassLoader loader = new IsolatedInterfaceLoader(parent);\n        return loader.loadClass(EXTRA_INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME);\n    }\n\n    private static void ignoreNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static boolean hasUnsupportedFeatureErrorCause(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error error && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    public interface IsolatedExtraInterface {}\n\n    private static class IsolatedInterfaceLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        IsolatedInterfaceLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    if (EXTRA_INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                        loadedClass = findClass(name);\n                    } else {\n                        loadedClass = super.loadClass(name, false);\n                    }\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!EXTRA_INTERFACE_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.findClass(name);\n            }\n            String resourceName = name.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream input = getParent().getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n                if (input == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n                }\n                byte[] classBytes = input.readAllBytes();\n                return defineClass(name, classBytes, 0, classBytes.length);\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name, exception);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 441, "output": 2904, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45841, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778773932575, "responseId": "resp_0c6114a654385776016a05efad01548190a806e751c52fe4c5"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_CQM8QRFzQWeW6jOT7kqCkzHs|fc_0c6114a654385776016a05efc885948190b8a44dadfddd7dd3", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 5258 bytes to tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778773968297}]}
